All Classes

Class Description
BasicMovingRule
Basic moving rule used to check if the move by the client was performed correctly
BasicSelectionRule
Basic selection rule used to check if the selection from the client was correct.
Board
Draws and colors the Trilma Board
CantMoveOutOfBaseRule  
Field
Abstract field on board, subtypes: inner field, base field.
Game
A game class for Trilma, executes commands, checks if the action is permitted by the rules, sends back commands to TrilmaClient
GameDAO
Used for checking the values of private fields in Game
GameInterface
Interface responsible for checking game rules on move or select by player.
IllegalMoveException
Exception thrown when player tries to perform illegal move action.
IllegalSelectionException
Exception thrown when player tries to perform illegal selection action.
JumpDistanceRule  
MovingRule
Abstract class for rule checking only validity of move action, does not modify select action.
Peg
Represents peg, has owner and color, possibly a visitor in Field (Visitor pattern)
Rule
Abstract class for decorating rule.
SelectionRule
Abstract class for rule checking only validity of select action, does not modify move action.
TrilmaClient
Trilma Client initializes a Frame for the Client, provides visuals and establishes connection with a server
TrilmaServer
A server class for Trilma, creates game, establishes connection through socket, adds players to game.
